{
  "_comment": "Per-base desecrated pool sizes. KEY MODEL CORRECTION: 'no desecrated prefixes' on armour means there are no armour-EXCLUSIVE (lord) desecrated prefix mods \u2014 but Omen of Putrefaction still creates 3 prefix slots, and on armour those prefix REVEALS draw from the NORMAL prefix pool (e.g. boots reveal Movement Speed/Life as desecrated prefixes). So 'desec_prefix_from_normal' marks bases whose putrefaction prefix slots roll the normal prefix pool. Suffix slots draw from the small desecrated/lord suffix pool. Verified bases read from PoE2DB per-base pages; run verify_desecrated.py to confirm others.",
  "_facts_confirmed": "PoE2 wiki (current): Omen of Putrefaction replaces all mods with up to 6 unrevealed desecrated mods (5 if fractured) and corrupts. Lord pools (Ulaman/Amanamu/Kurgal) are LARGE (~60-70 mods each, mixed archetypes); lord-forcing restricts reveals to one lord's pool but that pool is still big \u2014 the per-base RELEVANT subset is what matters. ilvl 65+ and Preserved+ bones required for lord mods. 0.5: desecrated Instant Leech can no longer roll.",
